    • Method Detail

      • parseAST

        public FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST parseAST(AbstractSyntaxAST parentAST,
                                            SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        This method will parse the FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST with the given parameters. The only AST which can parse a FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST is the RootSyntaxAST, because you can't define a function inside a BlockSyntaxAST or something else.

        An example for this statement:

             @native[default]
     fun println<>(message: string);
        Note that a FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST can be native and so it doesn't need any block besides a semicolon to mark the end of the function definition.
        Overrides:
        parseAST in class AbstractStatementSyntaxAST
        Parameters:
        parentAST - the AbstractSyntaxAST for the parent check and error throwing.
        syntaxAnalyzer - the SyntaxAnalyzer which should be used to parse this FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST
        Returns:
        the parsed FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST or null if something went wrong

      • printSyntaxAST

        public void printSyntaxAST(java.io.PrintStream printStream,
                           java.lang.String indents)
        Description copied from class: AbstractSyntaxAST
        This method will be overwritten by the classes which extends AbstractSyntaxAST. It will print with help of the PrintStream and indents a tree which is used for debugging. To print all RootSyntaxASTs you just need to call this method ArkoiCompiler.printSyntaxTree(PrintStream).
        Overrides:
        printSyntaxAST in class AbstractStatementSyntaxAST
        Parameters:
        printStream - the PrintStream which should get used for the output.
        indents - the indents which will make the AST look like a Tree.

      • hasAnnotation

        public boolean hasAnnotation(java.lang.String annotationName)
        This method loops through all annotation and returns true if it found an annotation with the defined name.
        Parameters:
        annotationName - The name which is used to search if the annotation is present.
        Returns:
        It will return false if the list is empty or it doesn't found anything. Otherwise it will just return true.
